overview.text: Expansive, waterfront Peruvian restaurant serving ceviche and other seafood dishes, plus cocktails.

description.text:
Upscale Peruvian eatery set on Pier 1 1/2 in the Embarcadero neighborhood with bay views.
The large venue features a bar and outdoor seating on the waterfront patio. It's popular for lunch and dinner, and reservations are recommended. People say the staff is attentive.
The menu focuses on seafood. Popular dishes include empanadas, ceviche, and lomo saltado. Guests also like the pisco sours and the desserts.
Visitors praise the location, the atmosphere, and the views.
Customers typically spend $50–100.

text.text:
Fine dining Greek restaurant with excellent service and high quality food. To start off, I had calamari (which was not fried) and the server brought out some bread and oil. This was stuffed with cheese and drizzled with a light olive oil sauce. Very unique way to cook squid and it was absolutely amazing. I wished there were more than 6 on the plate! Kokkari had a pork chop special the other night roasting over the fire and it was melt in your mouth kind of good. Might’ve been the best pork I’ve ever had since there was a lot of love and care put into this cut of meat. Wine selection was vast and detailed. The waiter helped me pick a popular Greek red wine. Dessert was phenomenal and I can’t even remember the name of it. I’ve always wanted to try this dessert and the plate they bring out is picture perfect, had to get it! (Pictured below)

Overall, I’d come back here for special occasions and spontaneous, luxurious nights out, if I lived here. 10/10, great job Kokkari!

text.text:
Kokkari Estiatorio offers an exceptional Greek dining experience in San Francisco. The food was excellent, with authentic flavors and high-quality ingredients shining through in every dish.

Our server, Frank, truly elevated the meal with his attentive service and expert knowledge. His wine recommendations were spot-on, perfectly complementing our food choices and enhancing the overall dining experience. Frank's familiarity with the menu and ability to guide us through our selections demonstrated a deep understanding of Greek cuisine and the restaurant's offerings.

The ambiance at Kokkari strikes a balance between upscale and welcoming, making it suitable for both special occasions and more casual nights out. Kokkari Estiatorio, with standout staff like Frank, proves itself as a top destination for Greek cuisine in the Bay Area.

editorialSummary.text: Contemporary, family-style outlet serving Cantonese-style dishes with panoramic harbor views.

text.text:
We decided to host our reception dinner here because of the convenient location, amazing food, and a nice view with ferry building as the background. We reserved half of the dinner area and the outdoor patio for the party at night.

Tiffany was our event coordinator and she's amazing! She explained everything clearly and got back to us in a timely manner. Staffs at the dinner was very very patient throughout the whole event ~10pm. The service is #1. The manager of the bar even asked me to take a shot with him at the end. I was very surprised by the quality of the cocktail here. I loved the bartenders and they made the drinks super quick. The dessert table was a nice touch. I got no complains but tons of complements about the quality of the food. How fresh and how yummy they are.

text.text:
We made reservations for dinner on a Sat at 6:30pm and glad we did - it was bustling.

Order came to be about $110 for two, all included - but i think the quality ingredients and unpretentious, super attentive service is way worth it for special occasions.

You have to get their live steamed fish - and have it + sauce over rice! We also ordered the vegetarian goose + green beans (no pork), which were all tasty. If I had to nitpick, it’d just be that the green beans dish was a tad small for the price (we liked it too much).

editorialSummary.text: Contemporary waterside seafood eatery serving local oysters and clams, plus craft cocktails.

text.text:
I had the most amazing solo lunch at Hog Island Oyster Co. in San Francisco. Their mussels, infused with African flavors, were hands down the best I’ve ever tasted. Paired with the perfect glass of white wine, and all while overlooking the serene waters—it was an unforgettable midday escape. The setting was perfect for a leisurely break before continuing on a relaxed stroll along the waterfront. Highly recommend for anyone looking for delicious seafood and a scenic, laid-back experience!

PS This was my second visit here this trip
🩵🌊⛅️😉

text.text: All I wanted for my birthday this year was oysters. My cousin suggested this restaurant for my birthday lunch, knowing that I’m a hardcore lover of oysters. This has gone down as one of the best birthday lunches I’ve ever had. I started off with the savory oyster shooter, which was very tasty and satisfying. Although I typically get sweet and/or fruity drinks, this savory drink showed my tastebuds a great time. The 6 oysters that I ordered were truly phenomenal. Each one had a unique and refreshing taste. To no one’s surprise, I devoured the oysters. Finally, the rustic seafood stew was THE perfect dish. Out of all the seafood stews I have tried, this one tops them all. It was bursting with flavor and I couldn’t get enough. It was very fresh, high quality, and perfect in every way. This restaurant goes down as one of my top favorites for seafood, specifically oysters. I absolutely, most definitely, highly recommend.

text.text: Such a great experience here! Every single staff member we interacted with were so kind and helpful. We shared a number of the mezze plates. The asparagus salad with burrata was amazing and the lamb Kosta was delicious. Definitely get the Barcha spreads. We were curious about what was in one dish and the chef came over and explained everything with enthusiasm. He also told us about another dish we didn't order (the dumplings), but was a crowd favorite. Then he brought us over two dumplings to try! The servers heard it was my birthday so they brought over a piece of cake at the end of the night. The restaurant itself is beautiful and the service was excellent. Highly recommend!

editorialSummary.text: Chinese restaurant in the Rincon Center presenting dim sum in a warm, well appointed dining room.

text.text: Two of us ordered 9 dishes as we were a little excited. A little too much than our stomach can take. All dishes are great and better than most dim sum places in the south bay. Among the 9 dishes, we like dumplings, sesame balls, and bean curd roll a lot. Sesame balls are a little expensive at $15, but they are the best I have had so far (I like dessert a lot). The place is comfy, the dim sum carts are all around you. The jasmine tea uses true high quality tea leaves that is one of the best in Chinese restaurants I have been to. This place has been on the Michelin list twice (2016 and 2021). They deserve it.

text.text:
Yank Sink offers a nice variety of dim sum, both steamed and fried, that's sure to please dim sum enthusiasts. Conveniently located inside the mall, its dining area extends into the mall itself, creating a casual and relaxed atmosphere.

The service at Yank Sink is efficient, with dim sum carts making rounds for patrons to choose from. Additionally, they offer the option to order some items via QR code, adding a modern touch to the dining experience.

One of the best parts about Yank Sink is its reasonable prices. For just $70, two people can enjoy a satisfying meal without breaking the bank.

In summary, Yank Sink is a solid choice for dim sum lovers looking for a tasty and affordable dining experience in a relaxed setting.

overview.text: Relaxed spot offering traditional dim sum and other Chinese cuisine plus beer, wine and cocktails.

description.text:
Trendy dim sum restaurant in the Embarcadero's Rincon Center Garage serving Chinese comfort food for breakfast, brunch, lunch, and dinner.
The menu includes vegetarian and gluten-free options, plus small plates and desserts. Peking duck, soup dumplings, and custard tarts are popular dishes. There's a great tea selection, as well as beer, wine, and cocktails.
The lively atmosphere is good for kids, and the restaurant provides high chairs. There can be a wait; reservations are recommended for lunch. People say service is fast.
Customers typically spend $30–50.

text.text:
We had the best experience at STK on 1 Market St. We stumbled upon this place while walking around the Financial District late one evening. It was one of the only places open after 10 p.m., and there was a happy hour from 10-11 p.m., which was a pleasant surprise.

The decor was quite stunning and modern, and the place had great vibes even at that late hour. It was exactly the kind of late-night find we were hoping for.

We got seated right away, and the staff was attentive and helpful. They walked us through the menu, explained the happy hour, and made great suggestions on menu options.

We started with a Not Your Daddy’s Old Fashioned and the Fade to Blackberry—both highly recommended. Since it was late, we kept it simple and had the tater tots, crab cake, and skirt steak. Everything was cooked perfectly and absolutely delicious.

Overall, I highly recommend STK, especially if you’re looking for a late-night dinner.

description.text:

The menu features Venetian delights, including cicchetti and risotto, alongside wine and cocktails. People recommend the meatballs, the charcuterie board, and the tiramisu.
Set in a unique location, the cozy haunt features a cute coat closet and a gender-neutral restroom. Guests say the staff is attentive, helpful, and fun.
Customers typically spend $50–100.
